-- Hong Kong drawndown mortgage loans rise 8.8 pct in March from Feb
-- By Christina Lo
-- Fri Apr 25, 2014 06:48AM EDT
-- None



April 25 (Reuters) - New mortgage loans drawn down in Hong Kong totalled HK$13.5 billion ($1.74 billion) in March, up 8.8 percent from a month earlier, Hong Kong Monetary Authority (HKMA) data showed on Friday.

